I don't believe you can't ToT every 4 minutes in most places (with most mobs being pure melee), but hey if you say so I believe it. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No but you believe I can dire charm in every zone and at any encounter.  There a large numbers of casters in zones like Seb and Howling Stones.  Most of the new zones are filled with Shadowknights for some reason, so lots to tap there.  Just like there are places where dire charm absolutely owns, there are zones where TOT owns.  Picking which way you go about doing things is part of knowing your class.  Having abilities in some zones and not in others is part of balance, which is one of the main limiters of dire charm.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Originally posted by Soulcarver</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I don't believe you can consistently channel through a mob quading for 180, but if you say you can, I believe you.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Why stop at 180 you can charm newly created sentries in Sleepers Tomb they quad for 324.  Boks and other mobs I am citing from Sebilis on the other hand tend to hit a bit softer.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Originally posted by Soulcarver</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I wish you were on my server so that I could observe your work. Heck I'd love to group with you--exp would flow like water.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Do what the mages on my server do, form AOE groups and get an AA point every 90 minutes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Originally posted by Soulcarver</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
However, I tend to agree more with Lumine's assesment as being more realistic. Hey when you can almost buy it to a rock hopper you know there is inherent risk. And those things have almost NO MR.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Lumine's assesment is the same as mine in relation to groups and charming, I suggest you reread the post (though picking selective bits of information seems to be the way you try to argue your point).  In a place like the grey with run3/jboots, my chances of dying while charm solo'ing are pretty much zero.  Plus as pointed out about a thousand times we cannot heal our pets or charmed mobs.  Nobody would ever use dire charm to solo.  Charm solo'ing I never haste and I never slow, the idea is to have both mobs beat each other to 10% dispell charm and kill both.  Using either slow or haste causes one mob to have to much health towards the end.  Nowhere have I stated that dire charm doesn't absolutely own in some situations (I would expect to see higher level mobs in Kael shortly), but it is not even remotely to the level you make it out to be.  I also firmly believe that it will have little or no impact on my ability to consistently use a charmed mob to deal out damage in a group setting if it is removed from the game.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Originally posted by Soulcarver</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
If charming is so easy to accomplish (and maintain), then what you've demonstrated so deaftly is that charm itself is WAY over-powered; because the inherent risk/reward is WAY skewed in your favor. Nerf batter up???<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I do recall that my first post was mages have an issue with charm, not with dire charm.  Then again it has been that way since beta and you just noticed it now.  At least you pick the proper place to make an argument finally, though it is nice to see you base your entire self worth on the basis of what others can accomplish and you can't.  Charm/Mez have been slowly reduced in effect since release.  That is why Boltran's is level limited like it is same as dazzle.  I wasn't exactly thrilled when we got a whack in ROK but I can certainly see where it was warranted.  I think as I have said before we are right where we need to be at as a class.  Most other classes are balanced more closely with each other then in the past as well.  Certainly some more tweaking to be done, but best it has been ever in my book.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Originally posted by Soulcarver</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
So in true conclusion, I am very skeptical--but will tip my hat to you and say you are very skilled at what you do and leave it at that. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I am an average enchanter.  I can think of people over the years on my server and others who could and probably still can run circles around me.  Just because your basis of my class is somebody who went from LOIO to Dreadlands to Karnors to get level 60 doesn't mean that I have god like powers.  Take some time to read some of the parse logs being thrown up.  I have yet to see one which lists a dire charmed pet, though I have seen several which show mage/necro pets owning hybrids.<br>
<br>
